  h4.strong Terminology
  p PtGolf.us allows groups to kept a handicap based on some form of a #{link_to('Modified Stableford Scoring System','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stableford',class:"blue-link")}
  p Below is the definitions of the terms used in PtGolf.us
  dl.indent-dd.strong-dt
    dt Quota
    dd A player's quota is basically their handicap using a point scoring system.
    dd Like a handicap, it is computed by selecting and averaging recent scores. The standard golf handicap use the best 10 scores out of the last 20 rounds. (there are some adjustments for course slopes/ratings). The most used 'dog fight' scoring will just look at the last 10 rounds.
    dd PtGolf.us has group options that allow you to say how many rounds are used.  It also has options for dropping the high and low scores from the rounds selected and to round or truncate the computed quota.
