    dt Points Pulled
    dd The sum of your point score on each hole (or each side)
    dd The points pulled is what is entered for your score on each side and total points pulled is the sum of the sides.
    dt Plus/Minus
    dd The difference between your quota and points pulled in a round. If your quota is 27 points and your total points pulled is 24, your points Plus/Minus is -3.
    dt Dues
    dd Your entry fee for the game and/or side games. The purpose of Dues is to redistribute wealth!
    dt Players - Group Players - Participants - Members
    dd Since PtGolf.us and GolfGaggle.com has gone through many changes. Some of those changes included terminology changes. Some of the older terminology has crept into the current version. 
    dd
      ul
        li 
          | Player = Group Player = Member.  All are members of a group, or a players that play with a group. Group Player is the formal name. Player is short version.
        li Participants are Players that are Participating in an Event. Technically, Participant refers to an EventRound or a ScoredRound that links a Group Player with an Event.

    dt Teams
    dd Teams consist of 1 to 4 players (1 really being indiviual players).
    dd Execpt for indiviual teams, teams are set by <a href='about/forming'>a forming method</a> That method just provides options based on how many players are present (Individual, Twosomes, Threesomes, Foursomes, Mixed Twosomes and Threesomes, Mixed Threesomes and Foursome). How teams are formed consists of 4 options (Random, Seeded, ABCD Draw and ABCD Battle).


